          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measurement of binary and ternary",
                " events by a telescope detector without",
                " using a coincidence."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Telescope consisting of an E- and",
                " a dE- detector. The dE-detector was a Si(Au) surface",
                " barrier with a depleted zone of 26.7 microns",
                " thickness, a surface of 300. mm**2 and a resolution",
                " FWHM for the 5.486 MeV alpha-line of Am-241 of 35 keV.",
                " The E-detector had a depleted zone of 500 microns,",
                " a surface of 450 mm**2, and  a resolution of 40. keV.",
                "It was also a Si(Au) surface barrier detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".With this thickness of the dE-detector the signal for",
                " the Z=1 ternary particles is completely different",
                " from the one for the alpha particles which allows",
                " thus still particle identification.",
                ".Differences with formerly reported values are",
                " explained by the extrapolation to the lower energies",
                " of the alpha particle spectra which deviate",
                " from a Gaussian."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".In some cases the telescope was shielded with an",
                " Al-absorber of 20 microns thickness in order to reduce",
                " the damage by the fission fragment bombardment."
              ]
            }
          ],
